,Recommended,292910,26640011,"Posted: 16 November, 2016",all,Mr. Matt,"This is a set of the first three out of a four-game ""quadrilogy"" of point-and-click adventure games. They have silly but fun stories, a few memorable characters, some nice puzzles, and...some perplexing puzzles that mar the experience a bit. Over all, it's a good time and I do recommend these games, but don't expect to beat them without having to reference a walkthrough several times. I grew up playing point-and-click adventure games, yet I still had to look up solutions quite a bit, especially in the third game, ""Goodbye Deponia.""If you're interested, Deponia Doomsday is the fourth game, which is not contained in this pack. I really liked it as well, and would recommend it too, though you'll probably want to make sure you like the first three games, contained in this pack, before buying the fourth."
