76561198011967833,Recommended,292910,34641773,Posted: 31 August,all,Aotrs Commander,"I bought the trilogy recently in the sales, and it was a good 35-hour playthrough (that was a good start - for that sort of time, I could have paid full price and been happy). I very throughly enjoyed it and easily would put it on a level with the likes of the best of Monkey Island, Sam and Max and Hector Badge of Carnage.The songs that introduce each act is gloriously catchy.Difficulty-wise, I only occasionally had to resort to a walkthrough (but that's been true of literally every point-and-click game I've ever played!), but on the whole, the puzzles made sense, and even the walkthrough-bits was either that one thng I'd just missed somewhere or made perfect sense in hindsight. (I think there was only one puzzle in the entire trilogy I would have said was a little bit obscure, but even that is debatable.) There's a lot of variety, with little minigames and a few gimmicks that keep it all very interesting and the world and characters are charming.I feel I should comment on the ending, as it is a contentious point I saw in the other reviews; I didn't have a problem with it myself and felt it was fitting. I can't - shouldn't - say more than that, but we're not talking ME3-levels or anything here, in my opinion.Overall then, I can definitely recommend this game."
