76561198049271328,Recommended,292910,32905645,Posted: 27 June,all,NixasXV,"I highly recommend checking this trilogy out if you're a fan of humorous and well made point and click adventure games.I racked up 41 hours playing this which when divided roughly works out as 13 1/2 hours per game - I did listen to all of the dialogue and developer's commentary so your playtime may be shorter.The animation and art style are very slick and nice to look at, and the story is great. It is full of humour but actually manages to be touching as well. You may hate Rufus (the protagonist) but if you do then you're in good company, almost all the other characters hate him too :PI am really not okay with some of the things he did in the sewer during Goodbye Deponia. Poor June, poor Goon, and those poor children!Honestly I'm not sure what else to say other than that I enjoyed this immensely and am very very glad I picked it up (I even got it on sale which is just a bonus as I would have happily paid full price for what I got)I had the developer's commentary on throughout the game which I don't know if I'd recommend on your first playthrough or not - on the one hand it gives you some interesting insight into the development process and the commentary is also just funny in and of itself... but on the other hand I spoilt a few of the puzzle solutions and minor story plot points for myself by listening to the commentary too early on. It really depends on how you want to play, and you can always replay it for the commentary if that's what you want.There are a few little bugs here and there, but I found nothing that broke the game or hurt my enjoyment of it.Oh, and I guess the puzzles are pretty good too :PI do wish I hadn't known about Deponia Doomsday before playing this though - I would have definitely cried at the ending if I didn't already know that Rufus survives (or is cloned again I guess although with Hermes dead I'm not sure who would do that) and that he has the chance to find Goal and head for Elysium again. If I had played this before the 4th came out I would have been inconsolable, but instead I'm just excited to start playing Doomsday (which of course I have already purchased :P )"
