,Recommended,292910,14145165,"Posted: 24 January, 2015",all,LonM,"Deponia started off really well, and then turned into a bit of a disappointment.The initial story is quite good. You play the bumbling sociopath in his attempt to escape to a new life. Now, some people might find it hard to play a character who makes rather unethical decisions,  but that is the whole point of the game.It lets the sometimes dark humour flow much more easily and makes for a very enjoyable play through.However, even though the story started off well, I don't feel it was amazing. Especially towards the end more plot holes started showing, and the actual end of the game was extremely disappointing.The ending could have been easily solved with a minigame whereyou have to find some way of timing everyone to escape from the blades at the same time, and the dev commenter says that they really like minigames. What a missed opportunity that was.The ending also manages to negate any character development anyone could have had, as all the main characters pretty much have their lives screwed over.The puzzles in this game are generally pretty good, however in some cases the solutions ended up being extremely obscure and I had to find a walkthrough to prod me in the right direction. This was rather annoying, but for the most part the puzzle, item combination and minigames were designed well.The interface that goes along with the game has a good menu system, and a good inventory manager. The on-screen hints that show you where clicks are valid is also very helpful.The graphics in this game are extremely good, as is the soundtrack. It all really adds to the atmosphere and helps makes the exploring the game enjoyable.I did encounter many bugs while playing the game. None of them broke them game completely, but they were annoying. If you get stuck with characters not speaking scripted lines, pressing ""Esc"" solves this. Also, use the ""load"" button to load saves, not the ""continue"" button.[s]Overall, had this game made a few parts less obscure, or at least offered a few more hints at what to do, as well as had a different ending, I would have probably enjoyed it, but it just ended leaving a sour taste. Especially when the main character Rufus's story had built up so close to his final goal.[/s]OK. It seems as if the story is begin continued. Given a proper continuation, rather than the abrupt end we were left with, I can finally push my rating over to begin a positive one."
