,Recommended,292910,14710636,"Posted: 1 March, 2015",all,Thelastreturn,"Deponia is by far my most favorite game of all times. Not only does it have a really great story with lot's of humor and drama, it also has awesome 2D graphics and an immersing world full of unique characters.Let's start at the beginning, 'Deponia: The Complete Journey' is a click-and-point adventure with alot of minigames in between. The complete journey is a combined trilogy of 'Deponia', 'Chaos on Deponia' and 'Goodbye Deponia' in which you follow Rufus, our brave hero on his quest to save the world.Even though this is a really great game for a wide ranged audience be aware of the insane difficulty (if you don't want to search hours for a missed clue or impossible to crack minigame, I recommend using a walkthrough from time to time).Is it worth buying if you already have one or two of the deponia games? One word - YES! I already had the first part of the trilogy and there is one big difference between the individual games and The Complete Journey: Developers commentary. You might ask; Why would this make a big difference? Well first of all, the commentary is written by the creative director of Daedalic Entertainment Jan Müller-Michaelis better know as 'Poki'. Who gives the player not only a look behind the screens, but also hilarious facts and discussions between himself, other developers or characters of the game. Which all adds up quite a few hours to the playtime. Believe me after listening to him for a while, you would want to learn German to play the game in the original language.Even though I could continue to ramble onwards about the positive sides of this game, let's switch to it's negative points. Let me first start with saying that during my Journey through Deponia, I encountered a fair amount of bugs. Most of them small and only ennoying, there was also one big game breaking bug. But don't be afraid future inhabitants of Deponia, most of the bugs have already been squashed by regular patches.Conclusion: This is one of those games that after finishing it, you would want to forget everything about it, just so that you could play it again with the same anticipation as the first time. Definitely a recommendation!"
