,Not Recommended,292910,14085615,"Posted: 20 January, 2015",all,Freak_NL,"The Deponia trilogy is lovely drawn, has good voice-acting throughout, and quite a lot of nice puzzles. The world it describes really piques your interest. It has all the ingredients for a great point-and-click game.So why shouldn't you buy this game for the full price?Well, the game is very much story-driven, and the story is where the problem lies. The overall story itself is good, although it suffers from a really badly written ending. That alone does not warrant a negative review, but the devil is in the details. It feels as if a lot of the story details and puzzles were written without any concern for fitting in with the various characters' personalities. Deponia goes from touching kindness in one scene to ruthless human sacrifices in the other, all performed by the protagnist who is almost, but not quite, likable.The impression I got from this game was that it was created by a talented team of game developers… and the puerile nephew of their primary financer whom they could not refuse to hire.Get this game in the bargain bin during the summer or christmas sale though; it certainly has its good points."
