,Recommended,292910,19434502,"Posted: 2 December, 2015",all,IMainAsMissPauling,"This is my first review!  I've just been replaying this game after playing through it a few months ago.  The game is fantastic.  It is the best point-click adventure game I've played since Maniac Mansion back on the NES.  The characters are well developed, the play control is intuitive, the logic flow is tricky, but with just enough hints to get through.  The story is seriously clever. You get really sucked into the plot.  I started off buying just the first game.  At the end, I immediately bought this...I should've just bought this set from the start.The minor play control gripe I have is that the tutorial doesn't tell you that you in fact can skip a lot of the slow walking. If you are moving to a screen you've already been to, you can jump to it (sometimes called zip-mode) by just clicking the orange arrow a couple times.  Also, knowing that the space button reveals all the trigger items is a wonderful feature that, again, should've been in the opening tutorial.The only serious complaint I have is that the last I checked, you are unable to gift the game.  I tried sending it to a friend only to find that I couldn't...it's weird when you want to hand over money but are unable...If you like any of the classic Lucasarts or Doublefine games, seriously, just get this. Don't be scared by the fact that it's done by some random German game company you've never heard of. The english voice actors are all excellent, and the creator-sung song is catchy as Hell (Huzzah, it's catchy as Hell!)"
