,Not Recommended,292910,15019450,"Posted: 23 March, 2015",all,Biblin,"A promising first part and middling to fair second part leads into a krass, sexist and jaw-droppingly racist finale.If you're interested in the seperate games, Deponia isn't half bad. The puzzles are good, and sensible rather than obscure. The humour is reasonable and it has an enjoyable storyline.There is a slight undercurrent which, when viewed from the right angle and without the context of the final game could be mistaken for riské irony. For example the female love interest and primary plot thread called ""Goal"". Oh yes ha, I see what you did there. Very good.The second game suffers primarily from much poorer puzzles. A spattering of comedy accents which again, from an optimistic point of view, are treading the line but in good humour.Then we get to part 3, which features a heavily implied paedophile trying to lure children into his caravan, and selling a black woman to be a monkey for an organ grinder. No, really. That one screen (They're both on the same one) puts the entire trilogy in a completely different light and will leave you very uncomfortable for the (far too long) remainder. If you can stomach continuing at all.Deponia on it's own is decent if you can bury your head in the sand like a Frank Miller fan and pretend it's just good fun. But there's no way I could possibly recommend this after that kind of revelation."
