76561198040955960,Not Recommended,292910,13960923,"Posted: 12 January, 2015",all,Nebulon-B_Frigate_FTW,"An oldschool adventure game with modern graphics. You'll probably love it if you have plenty of nostalgia for the glory days, but as a newcomer, I found the game at best mildly interesting and at worst downright annoying.The gameplay here is weak due to extremely illogical inventory puzzles that only get worse as you near the end, and thus you essentially have to either spend hours trying every possible combination or read a step-by-step guide. The worst is the second acts of the first two parts, and the last act of the last, as they introduce too many items and too many locations at once, overwhelming you and effectively forcing use of a guide. Minigames, which are rather common, are a welcome change of pace, but are still at times nothing but frustration with little reward.The story is alright, but unfortunately, you play as the worst (most dishonest, sexist, egotistical, immature, narcissistic, and downright unlikable) character in the game. The humor is awful, due in perhaps no small part to a pretty much literal translation from German, as well as extreme repetition of things that were never funny in the first place.The visuals are great, and are by far the best part of the game.Steer clear unless the genre itself is sufficient for you."
