,Recommended,292910,13818249,"Posted: 3 January, 2015",all,Tallens,"This isn't the first point-and-click adventure I've played, but it won't certianly be my last.This was probably the most enjoyable game i've ever played, sinking 17 hours into it over three days.As seen in the title, this is the complete journey including Deponia 1, Deponia 2, and Deponia 3. As such, I'll be doing 3 small reviews, based on each game.Deponia:This is the first game, as you've probaby learned. It's got a bit of a corny feel in the beginning, but I quickly grew to like it, and understood that this game is not meant to be serious. It's got plenty of interesting characters, locations, and some great voice actors. While this game is pretty difficult after the first area, and I'm not ashamed to admit I used a walkthrough in alot of the game, I can see where it would be possible without them. It leaves off to a mediocre ending, but with the money gained from this, the company made the next two games brilliant.Deponia 2:With better cutscenes, music, writing and etc., It's a great sequel. With brilliant artwork, It kept me entranced, even through the slump that most media goes through in the middle episode. It keeps you excited from the very beginning, and kept me excited until the very end.Deponia 3:It's better in every way than either of the previous games. It's hard for me to talk about much without revealing the ending, plot twists, or anything really. It's an amazing game. Play all of them.Overall:These games are beautiful, immense, and deep. They are worth the price, and I am probably going to do another playthrough, listening to the developer commentary. Also, those ""Huzza!"" transitions are pretty amazing."
