76561198214213240,Recommended,292910,21381021,"Posted: 21 February, 2016",all,strawberrydream,"I bought Deponia a while ago when it was on sale, but just got around to playing it yesterday. I believe I just started the second part of the trilogy.Deponia is a point-and-click adventure game with futuristic and steampunk elements. The protagonist, Rufus, is a lazy scum bag who is perfectly happy mooching off others. However, due to events he finds himself wrapped in (partially by his own doing), he gets wrapped up in events much larger than himself and becomes the unlikely hero that the story needs.Seriously, I have almost nothing but good things to say about this game. The aesthetic is charming, cartoony, and with a soundtrack that captures the setting well. All of the characters are engaging and fun, especially Rufus, who does progress with the story. Voice work is good, and the characters have voices that suit them well.My one complaint is in the puzzles. Sometimes, the puzzles are too easy, where other times, there is no indicator in-game on how to reach the solution. Most of the time, trial and error worked well to get over hurdles.Overall, this game is great."
