,Recommended,292910,29122133,Posted: 8 January,all,Del Mingus,"TL:DR Deponia is a pretty good point and click game with some great characters and humour. A few of its puzzles can be a bit frustrating thoughFull Version:The Complete Journey collects together the first three Deponia games into one package with bonus features like Dev commentary and a quest log for example. Deponia is a pretty standard point and click game with a zany off the wall and occasionally dark humour.The main character Rufus is a massive loser who creates chaos and destruction wherever he goes. However his ego is so overinflated he still thinks he's a great guy.That sounds like an awful choice for a main character but I found Rufus to be quit likeable despite his flaws and he's a great character. The rest of Deponias cast of characters are all wild and wacky enough to make the game entertaining.As I said above the gameplay is the standard point and click variety. Pick up items and either combine or use them on other stuff to progress through the game, with the occasional mini game popping up.Good points:- the complete version collects the first 3 games together with bonus features as icing on the cake. So you get more bang for you buck than you would by buying the games seperately- Rufus despite being an awful person becomes quite a likeable and entertaining protaganist. The rest of the games cast features loads of strange and entertaining characters as well that add to the games charm- I like the fact that this game is more aimed at adults with a more crude and dark humour than your typical point and click game.Bad points:- a few of the games puzzles are quite frustrating and at times very obtuse or over complicated. For example, without spoiling anything, there was a puzzle that you could only solve by going into the settings and turning off the music. The game only gives you a very vague hint about this and while I'm sure the Devs thought it was a clever and unique solution it felt so out of the box that it was a bit of a pisstake. Fortunately most of the puzzles arent too bad and can be solved with enough investigation or exploring."
