,Recommended,292910,28827289,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,Let'sJoinTheRiverDance,"First thing one should know before playing this game: At the start the main protagonist will come off as a total♥♥♥♥♥♥ A real self centered, egotistical ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥, whose antics would make an SJW's balls recede into its body and come out the ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥. But that's what makes him likeable and unique from other cookie-cut 'good' main characters. And your opinion of him will most likely get better anyway as his character develops, which is par for the course as the story progresses.Second: Like most point and click adventure games, the nature of its interaction mechanics and stuff crafting will present you with problems whose solutions follow some dumb frustrating logic. There were many times where I got stuck on a screen because I didn't point this one specific thing to this other specific inconspicuous thing that no one would think would go together in the first place.So Third: Save yourself some time and go look at a walkthrough once you see that no option you'd thought of would progress the game. If you thought that you've exhausted all possible combinations of all the crap in your inventory and environment, there's no point in being stubborn and keep clicking the same things over and over when the solution's something minor you probably simply overlooked. Sure you would have found it eventually, but you would have also wasted your time.Lastly: Don't take it too seriously, and enjoy! Every character is quirky, the world is interesting, and it's got a ton of fun minigames. It's got a lot of really funny ridiculous moments, and some really dark moments and mature themes too. So it's a real rollercoaster ride, and gets a solid thumbs up from me."
